RACE.FOOTNOTES: STARSHIP LEGEND stalked in the four path, was roused around the far turn and bid from the four path entering the lane, lugged in just before the eighth pole, was corrected and ran on to lead going into the final furlong, began to drift out late, but held on to win. MORGAN'S BLUFF brushed with an outer foe at the start, was held up in midpack from the three path, was under right handed urging in the two path turning into the lane was short of room and angled out to the four path passing the eighth pole, and finished evenly. AMERICAN ODALISQUE set the pace in the two path, was roused when headed along the rail around the far turn, but yielded going into the final furlong. LIPARI was reserved in the five path early, was ridden in the seven path turning into the lane, but was no factor. BREAKING BULLET brushed with an inner foe at the start, raced prominently in the three path, was cued to bid going into the far turn, briefly lead turning into the stretch, but was in tight passing the eighth pole, and faded. UPSTREET checked going into the first turn, tracked in the two path, was ridden around the far turn, but gaveway entering the lane.
